    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.5.0 0.5.1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, 8.2.3428\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nGentoo Linux 2.8 , Kernel 5.10.75\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkonsole/yakuake 21.08.2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nCompiled via portage/emerge\n\n### How to reproduce the issue\n\nnvim --clean\r\n:e ANY_LARGE_TEXT_FILE\r\n:vs ANY_LARGE_TEXT_FILE\r\nuse any scrolling method to reach the top/bottom of the screen\r\nkeep scrolling\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nOnly the currently selected buffer scrolls its file.\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nOnce the edge of the visible buffer is reached, both open buffers start scrolling synchronously (accompanied by rendering artifacts and missing chunks of the file in the non-selected buffer).\r\n\r\nI checked with \":windo verbose set\", nothing there is causing this.\r\n\r\nMight be related to [Issue 15692](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/15692)",
