            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "> Hi all,\r\n> \r\n> I am experimenting the same issue. However, I have observed that if I set the `$TERM` variable to a different value, it works for me. For instance, setting $TERM to `tmux-256color` works, even if I am not using tmux. The same happens if you are using terminal a emulator like [kitty](https://sw.kovidgoyal.net/kitty/), which uses `xterm-kitty` by default.\r\n> \r\n> To be honest, I do not know if this information is useful at all.\r\n\r\nThe issue does seem to be caused by the $TERM variable.  With `tmux-256color` I got even more spectacular graphical artifacting, but `konsole-256color` seems to have resolved it for me.  This is really strange, though, since I've been using `xterm-256color` for almost two years now without issues.",
