            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "> Can it be a dependency problem? I don't know much about Gentoo Linux, but I cannot reproduce this on Arch Linux in Konsole with either Neovim v0.6.0-dev or v0.5.1. Or I may have misunderstood what you meant by `ANY_LARGE_TEXT_FILE` and `scrolling method`.\r\n\r\nCould be, but I'm not sure where to start tracking that down, since neovim compiles and runs just fine otherwise.\r\nI meant open any file with enough content that you have to scroll through it, then `vsplit` to open the same or another similarly large file.  By scrolling method I meant `h, j, k, l`, arrow keys, mouse wheel, etc.\r\n\r\nI should also note that the issue was specifically visual artifacting of the contents of the split windows; only the currently selected window actually had incrementing/decrementing line numbers to indicate 'real' scrolling.",
