        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I know this is an old ticket, but I seem to be having this issue when using this version in Windows using mintty 3.8.2 (bundled with Git Bash):\n```\nNVIM v0.12.2\nBuild type: Release\nLuaJIT 2.1.1774638290      \n```\n\nI installed nvim using `winget`, and the `$TERM=xterm`.\n\nFor more context:\n```\n$ bash --version\nGNU bash, version 5.3.9(1)-release (x86_64-pc-cygwin)\nCopyright (C) 2025 Free Software Foundation, Inc.\nLicense GPLv3+: GNU GPL version 3 or later <http://gnu.org/licenses/gpl.html>\n```\n\n```\n$ git --version\ngit version 2.54.0.windows.1\n```\n\nCuriously, running from cmd or powershell terminal works fine. In those terminal sessions, running `echo $TERM` returns the empty string, and not `xterm` like launching when launching Git Bash directly.\n\nThis is probably an integration issue with MinTTY, which I'm sure is outdated compared to anything Linux native. As a citizen of both OS's, this is a pain point for me, and likely for other would be neovim users forced by circumstance to develop on Windows.\n\nPlease let me know if there is anything I can do to help debug this issue further.\n",
